headline: KMX Q1 Earnings: CarMax Matches Revenue Expectations, Misses Profit Targets Amid Shifting Market Dynamics
summary: Used automotive vehicle retailer Carmax (NYSE:KMX) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 6.7% year on year to $6 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.60 per share was 8.6% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
